===Etymology===
Variant of {{och-l|廌|tr=dreʔ}} ({{w|Guangyun}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2009}}). If true, see there for etymology.

{{zh-ref|Janhunen (2011)}} instead suggests that {{lang|zh|豸}} and {{lang|zh|廌}} possibly had denoted different animals, yet were confused so they would be used seemingly interchangeably to refer to the same range of vague folkloric and mythological beasts.

{{zh-ref|Valenti (2018)}} posits a possible punning link between {{och-l|豸|tr=(d)reʔ}} and {{och-l|踟|tr=(d)re|to walk hesitantly}}.

{{rfe|zh|If not just a variant of {{och-l|廌|tr=dreʔ}}, then might {{och-l|豸|tr=dreʔ}} be related to {{cog|bo|དྲེད||bear}}? Old Chinese *''-ʔ'' occasionally corresponds to Old Tibetan ''-d'' in these cognate sets: {{och-l|我}} vs. {{cog|bo|ངེད||I; we}}, {{och-l|靡}} vs. {{cog|bo|མྱེད||not exist}}, etc.}}

